properties.areaDesc: Northern Humboldt Coast; Coastal Del Norte
properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued January 9 at 11:00PM PST until January 11 at 7:00PM PST by NWS Eureka CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...A large northwest swell will bring a threat for large
breaking waves to area beaches on Saturday. Breakers of 24 to
27 ft will be possible on west and northwest facing beaches.

* WHERE...Coastal Del Norte and Northern Humboldt Coast Counties.

* WHEN...From 7 AM to 7 PM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Large breaking waves will generate hazardous
conditions on area beaches. This threat will be maximized on
steeply sloped beaches. Large breaking waves can cause injury,
wash people off beaches and rocks, and capsize small boats
near shore.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A high tide above 8 ft midday on Saturday
may help to bring minor coastal flooding to select areas
around Humboldt county, particularly Centerville Beach.
properties.instruction:
A High Surf Advisory means that high surf will affect beaches in
the advisory area, producing rip currents and localized beach
erosion.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM TO 7 PM PST SATURDAY
